They are also following the call of their charismatic leader, Mr Miron Cosma, the man who led them on protests to Bucharest and secured their earlier wage increases. The strike seems motivated by a number of factors. The ministry further argues that the miners are in danger of pricing their coal out of the market. The miners' position seems untenable. COALMINERS from Romania's Jiu Valley, who spearheaded violent anti-reform rampages through Bucharest in 1990 and 1991, are once again out on strike, pressing the government for higher wages. 